interests: Hiking, Playing guitar, Comic book collecting, Painting, Learning languages
summary:
The user, Taylor Lee, is a 28-year-old non-binary individual who is gay and resides in Los Angeles, California. They are a graduate of the University of Michigan and work as a Graphic Designer in the tech industry. They love to go hiking, play guitar, collect comic books, paint, and learn languages. They identify as agnostic and politically liberal. Although they currently do not have children and do not wish to have any, they share their home with a cat. 

Taylor is interested in a long-term monogamous relationship with gay individuals between the ages of 25 to 35. They appreciate a partner who does not smoke and maintains an active lifestyle. They themselves follow a similar lifestyle - exercising regularly and indulging in alcoholic beverages occasionally while refraining from smoking and use of marijuana or other drugs. They are an adventurous, empathetic, humorous and equality-valuing Leo-born ENFP in Myers-Briggs Typology.
